prerequirements
---------------
- Cordon the nodes.
  kubectl cordon node <node_name>
- Make sure we go through the release notes.
  https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/tree/master/CHANGELOG
- Understand EKS cluster upgrades are irreversable.
- Test it in lower environments first.
- Before upgrading, Control plane and node groups should be on same version.
- Atleast 5 available ip addresses in the subnets.

Process To Follow
-----------------
- Upgrade control plane.
- Upgrade node groups/nodes/fargate profiles.
- Upgrade addons.
- Sometime EKS upgrade will make us to upgrade operators like helm, prometheus etc.,
